Hi Alin,

Thanks for your support!

The agent deployment through JAMF was successful after updating the script, and we tested it on a few other laptops as well.

Quick question—We're using the ScaleFusion MDM solution to manage our Windows devices. However, when we tried pushing the Endpoint Protector through ScaleFusion, we encountered the same server communication issue we faced with JAMF.

Would a script be required for Windows deployment as well? If you have any documentation on deploying the Windows agent via MDM, could you please share it?
 


Best regards,
Rajesh Kumar
IT Administrator @ SpotDraft

Thank you for your email.
I had the meeting with Rajesh Kumar and the issue was resolved in that session, I was waiting for him to get back to me after he deployed it for 2-3 other computers.

We tried the deployment with a different script and it worked as expected, the EPP client is now communicating with the server.
Please let me know after you test it out for some other computer if everything is fine and we can close the ticket.

Hi Alin,

We’ve already added the required steps in the System Extension settings
within Jamf, but the issue persists as I mentioned in my previous email.

After installing the EPP agent on endpoints, the Slack app either stops
working or loads very slowly. This is preventing users from catching up on
new messages in real time, which is critical for us.

I confirmed that unchecking Slack in the Content Aware policy resolves the
issue.

Please take a look.
